1
00:01:26,960 --> 00:01:29,840
<i>You must have talked</i>
<i>so many thieves out of their lifestyle.</i>

2
00:01:29,920 --> 00:01:31,680
Gorgeous, if you'd only love me,

3
00:01:31,760 --> 00:01:33,040
I'd leave my wife.

4
00:01:33,120 --> 00:01:34,520
Come here.

5
00:01:34,600 --> 00:01:35,720
Hey, wait. Hey.

6
00:01:37,560 --> 00:01:39,200
I won't let Mr. Yai

7
00:01:39,280 --> 00:01:40,760
lose to them ever again.

8
00:01:45,800 --> 00:01:47,840
<i>I'm just gonna lie here for a while.</i>

9
00:01:47,920 --> 00:01:49,080
<i>It's not often</i>

10
00:01:49,160 --> 00:01:50,760
I come across a bed this soft.

11
00:02:05,720 --> 00:02:06,560
Manager.

12
00:02:14,840 --> 00:02:15,920
Don't let me find out

13
00:02:16,520 --> 00:02:19,680
you were pulling a stunt
and sent your people to rob my boss.

14
00:02:22,480 --> 00:02:25,160
I wouldn't dare, I swear.

15
00:02:26,360 --> 00:02:28,560
Then don't forget. You have one month.

16
00:02:29,080 --> 00:02:30,600
Tell your madam

17
00:02:30,680 --> 00:02:33,360
to hurry up and pay back
the remaining debt to the boss.

18
00:02:34,160 --> 00:02:35,680
Otherwise, I'll be coming for you.

19
00:02:39,760 --> 00:02:40,680
Let's go.

20
00:03:20,080 --> 00:03:21,800
Uh, it's hot in here.

21
00:03:21,880 --> 00:03:23,160
Do you have a fan, gorgeous?

22
00:03:23,240 --> 00:03:24,640
Bring it over for me.

23
00:03:25,800 --> 00:03:28,200
Uh, yeah. I have one.

24
00:03:28,800 --> 00:03:29,720
Right here.

25
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:32,440
You're taking too long.

26
00:03:32,520 --> 00:03:34,960
Don't get on my bad side, gorgeous.

27
00:03:36,840 --> 00:03:37,880
Huh?

28
00:03:40,840 --> 00:03:43,080
I just remembered the fan is broken.

29
00:03:43,160 --> 00:03:44,040
Don't talk back to me.

30
00:03:44,120 --> 00:03:47,080
No, the fan is really broken.

31
00:03:47,160 --> 00:03:48,560
I haven't had time to get it fixed.

32
00:03:49,560 --> 00:03:51,000
A big house and there's only one fan?

33
00:03:51,080 --> 00:03:52,040
Why not buy a new one?

34
00:03:53,600 --> 00:03:55,600
I'm just a maid.

35
00:03:56,120 --> 00:03:58,520
I need to cut costs for my boss
whenever possible.

36
00:04:02,200 --> 00:04:03,720
A true angel, huh?

37
00:04:03,800 --> 00:04:06,680
Beautiful, kind, and virtuous.

38
00:04:09,600 --> 00:04:10,920
Come here, then.

39
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:15,240
Come here.

40
00:04:22,600 --> 00:04:23,840
Take off my clothes.

41
00:04:29,720 --> 00:04:31,000
If you do anything to me,

42
00:04:31,520 --> 00:04:33,080
I'll kill myself.

43
00:04:33,960 --> 00:04:35,400
I'm serious.

44
00:04:37,640 --> 00:04:39,640
Oh, come on.

45
00:04:40,240 --> 00:04:43,800
It's so hot. I've been on the run
from the police for three days and nights.

46
00:04:43,880 --> 00:04:44,840
This shirt…

47
00:04:47,640 --> 00:04:49,320
It's basically salted fish.

48
00:04:49,400 --> 00:04:51,520
Well, you choose.

49
00:04:53,120 --> 00:04:54,120
Take it off for me,

50
00:04:54,880 --> 00:04:57,080
or I'll go out and shoot the workers.

51
00:04:57,160 --> 00:04:58,520
I still have plenty of bullets.

52
00:05:41,240 --> 00:05:42,840
Were you trying to reopen the old cut?

53
00:05:44,640 --> 00:05:47,600
No, I didn't mean to.

54
00:05:50,840 --> 00:05:52,480
Or were you trying to tease me?

55
00:05:53,400 --> 00:05:57,000
Well, well. You look calm on the outside,

56
00:05:57,080 --> 00:05:58,400
but inside,

57
00:05:59,280 --> 00:06:00,640
you're a volcano.

58
00:06:02,840 --> 00:06:04,200
Come here.

59
00:06:07,400 --> 00:06:08,880
I said come here.

60
00:06:41,800 --> 00:06:43,000
Pin.

61
00:06:47,840 --> 00:06:49,840
You want a hole in your pretty tummy?

62
00:06:51,200 --> 00:06:52,800
I'm not joking.

63
00:06:55,560 --> 00:06:56,680
Close the window.

64
00:07:07,800 --> 00:07:09,360
Pin, is something wrong?

65
00:07:13,080 --> 00:07:14,800
No, nothing.

66
00:07:14,880 --> 00:07:16,520
I'm going to bed.

67
00:07:16,600 --> 00:07:19,160
I have to visit my mom
early tomorrow morning.

68
00:07:22,440 --> 00:07:23,320
Sleep well, Pin.

69
00:07:37,920 --> 00:07:39,160
Come sit next to me.

70
00:07:55,040 --> 00:07:56,560
Please don't do anything to me.

71
00:07:57,880 --> 00:08:00,000
The workers will all be asleep soon.

72
00:08:00,520 --> 00:08:02,320
You can leave then.

73
00:08:02,840 --> 00:08:05,320
I won't tell anyone you were in my room.

74
00:08:06,200 --> 00:08:08,600
I'll tell you when I want to leave.

75
00:08:19,320 --> 00:08:20,680
Don't upset me.

76
00:08:44,360 --> 00:08:45,560
Come closer.

77
00:09:01,440 --> 00:09:04,480
I don't want to hear sad stories.
I won't be able to sleep.

78
00:09:05,480 --> 00:09:08,280
I'll just let you sing for me, gorgeous.

79
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:09,840
Huh?

80
00:09:11,440 --> 00:09:14,080
A lullaby, any song.

81
00:09:14,160 --> 00:09:15,920
I have trouble sleeping.

82
00:09:16,440 --> 00:09:18,800
I need someone to lull me to sleep.

83
00:09:23,320 --> 00:09:25,040
I can't sing.

84
00:09:29,120 --> 00:09:31,120
If you don't want to sing…

85
00:09:35,280 --> 00:09:36,840
do you want to make other sounds?

86
00:09:39,800 --> 00:09:41,800
This gentle,

87
00:09:43,280 --> 00:09:45,400
fragrant lap

88
00:09:46,240 --> 00:09:48,920
makes me

89
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:53,040
- really want to--
- <i>Moon, oh, moon</i>

90
00:09:53,120 --> 00:09:57,040
<i>I wish for rice and curry</i>

91
00:09:57,120 --> 00:10:00,840
<i>I wish for a copper ring</i>

92
00:10:00,920 --> 00:10:04,080
<i>For my little one's hand</i>

93
00:10:04,160 --> 00:10:08,120
<i>I wish for an elephant, for a steed</i>

94
00:10:08,200 --> 00:10:11,880
<i>For my little one to ride on</i>

95
00:10:12,400 --> 00:10:15,320
<i>I wish for a little chair</i>

96
00:10:15,880 --> 00:10:19,120
<i>For my little one to sit on</i>

97
00:10:21,440 --> 00:10:28,320
<i>I wish for a bed, for a mattress</i>
<i>For my little one to sleep on</i>

98
00:10:28,840 --> 00:10:35,760
<i>I wish for a play</i>
<i>For my little one to enjoy</i>

99
00:10:35,840 --> 00:10:42,520
<i>I wish for a kind grandma</i>
<i>To care for my little one</i>

100
00:10:43,040 --> 00:10:49,920
<i>And I wish for a generous grandma</i>
<i>To care for me</i>

101
00:12:48,960 --> 00:12:51,960
MR. NA'S ARRIVAL

102
00:13:26,480 --> 00:13:27,600
Na, you bastard.

103
00:13:56,320 --> 00:13:57,520
The money is all there…

104
00:14:03,440 --> 00:14:04,760
Mr. Na's photo…

105
00:14:05,360 --> 00:14:06,680
Where's Mr. Na's photo?

106
00:14:15,280 --> 00:14:17,120
MR. NA'S ARRIVAL

107
00:14:29,600 --> 00:14:32,320
Hello, Jin. How's Mom doing?

108
00:14:34,800 --> 00:14:35,640
The surgery bill…

109
00:14:57,000 --> 00:14:57,840
Hey.

110
00:14:58,360 --> 00:15:00,200
Load as many sheep
onto the truck as possible.

111
00:15:00,280 --> 00:15:01,480
Quickly.

112
00:15:01,560 --> 00:15:03,680
Looks like there'll be multiple trips.

113
00:15:04,320 --> 00:15:05,160
There they are.

114
00:15:06,520 --> 00:15:07,600
Hey, wait.

115
00:15:08,240 --> 00:15:09,680
Who are you? Where did you come from?

116
00:15:09,760 --> 00:15:11,120
How can you just take the sheep?

117
00:15:11,200 --> 00:15:13,400
Tough guy, huh?

118
00:15:13,480 --> 00:15:15,000
I work for Mr. Teera.

119
00:15:15,080 --> 00:15:16,680
He told us to move the sheep.

120
00:15:16,760 --> 00:15:18,320
Is there a problem?

121
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:21,520
That's funny. I don't believe it.

122
00:15:21,600 --> 00:15:22,840
Trying to use the manager's name?

123
00:15:22,920 --> 00:15:23,960
Well, I'm not buying it.

124
00:15:24,560 --> 00:15:25,840
Then suit yourself.

125
00:15:25,920 --> 00:15:27,520
We don't care one bit.

126
00:15:30,640 --> 00:15:31,680
Let's go, Kan!

127
00:15:33,160 --> 00:15:35,120
Where are we going? We're already here.

128
00:15:35,640 --> 00:15:37,320
Go open the pen!

129
00:15:39,800 --> 00:15:41,800
- Hey.
- Hey!

130
00:15:42,680 --> 00:15:43,520
You can't go in.

131
00:15:49,080 --> 00:15:51,480
- Using a broom, huh?
- No!

132
00:16:04,640 --> 00:16:07,280
- You…
- No, don't! Don't do it!

133
00:16:08,360 --> 00:16:09,160
Don't what?

134
00:16:09,240 --> 00:16:11,080
I haven't done anything to you!

135
00:16:20,640 --> 00:16:22,360
Let go of me. Let go.

136
00:16:25,240 --> 00:16:26,320
Looking for a fight?

137
00:16:34,640 --> 00:16:36,520
- Uncle Win!
- Hey!

138
00:16:41,560 --> 00:16:43,160
If you guys have any problems,

139
00:16:44,120 --> 00:16:45,840
go talk to Manager Teera!

140
00:16:46,600 --> 00:16:50,480
But if you wanna talk
to my bullets first, so be it.

141
00:16:52,480 --> 00:16:53,480
Open the gate!

142
00:17:01,480 --> 00:17:02,680
Open it!

143
00:18:05,400 --> 00:18:08,920
Hey! Are you dead or what,
lying in the middle of the road like that?

144
00:18:11,680 --> 00:18:14,280
Get out of here, you lunatic!

145
00:18:15,640 --> 00:18:17,680
Kan, take care of him.

146
00:18:31,120 --> 00:18:32,200
Hey.

147
00:18:32,880 --> 00:18:34,080
Who the hell are you?

148
00:18:34,680 --> 00:18:36,040
Wanna become a ghost that guards the road?

149
00:18:55,040 --> 00:18:56,120
Whoa.

150
00:18:56,920 --> 00:18:58,160
I'm sorry, bro.

151
00:18:58,240 --> 00:19:00,040
I don't know what I did wrong.

152
00:19:00,640 --> 00:19:02,240
You're blocking my way.

153
00:19:04,040 --> 00:19:04,960
Oh?

154
00:19:05,480 --> 00:19:09,240
Oh, so this truck belongs
to the farm you just drove out of?

155
00:19:09,840 --> 00:19:10,800
Yeah.

156
00:19:11,320 --> 00:19:13,800
Ever heard of Manager Teera?

157
00:19:13,880 --> 00:19:15,600
If you don't want any trouble,

158
00:19:15,680 --> 00:19:17,440
get your filthy face out of here.

159
00:19:17,520 --> 00:19:18,720
Go!

160
00:19:18,800 --> 00:19:20,600
Come on, bro. I'm tired.

161
00:19:20,680 --> 00:19:22,560
Can't I sit and rest my legs for a bit?

162
00:19:22,640 --> 00:19:24,040
Wait a little more, alright?

163
00:19:24,120 --> 00:19:25,560
But if you can't wait,

164
00:19:25,640 --> 00:19:27,760
you can just carry that ten-wheeler

165
00:19:27,840 --> 00:19:29,400
over my head.

166
00:19:29,480 --> 00:19:31,000
No worries, okay?

167
00:19:33,880 --> 00:19:34,840
Hey, what?

168
00:19:37,160 --> 00:19:39,400
This is what I call being a smartass.

169
00:19:50,520 --> 00:19:52,040
You're such a loser.

170
00:20:03,320 --> 00:20:04,600
You think you're tough?

171
00:20:06,720 --> 00:20:08,400
Oh, hold on, bro. Easy.

172
00:20:08,480 --> 00:20:11,760
Calm down, bro. Let's talk.
I'm not doing anything to you. Easy.

173
00:20:11,840 --> 00:20:13,320
- I surrender.
- Ouch!

174
00:20:30,320 --> 00:20:31,720
1.2 million?

175
00:20:32,360 --> 00:20:33,640
I've calculated

176
00:20:34,160 --> 00:20:36,040
that if we sell all the animals,

177
00:20:36,120 --> 00:20:37,640
we'll instantly have cash in our hands.

178
00:20:38,280 --> 00:20:41,160
And we won't have to spend money
on their feed anymore.

179
00:20:43,720 --> 00:20:47,560
That's brilliant. You're the best.

180
00:20:49,000 --> 00:20:50,240
Also…

181
00:20:50,840 --> 00:20:52,600
after demolishing the animal pens,

182
00:20:53,440 --> 00:20:56,000
we could even set up our own gambling den
and open it on the farm.

183
00:20:56,080 --> 00:20:57,720
No one will come to check.

184
00:20:57,800 --> 00:21:01,320
The resort's guests are all VIPs as well.

185
00:21:01,840 --> 00:21:02,920
I'd say

186
00:21:03,760 --> 00:21:04,840
money will pour in.

187
00:21:06,080 --> 00:21:08,360
You're such a smart guy.

188
00:21:08,440 --> 00:21:10,720
No wonder
you're the manager of Paisal Farm.

189
00:21:10,800 --> 00:21:12,760
I chose the right person.

190
00:21:16,760 --> 00:21:17,960
Then I should ask for a reward.

191
00:21:23,000 --> 00:21:25,920
Though…

192
00:21:26,000 --> 00:21:27,760
this year

193
00:21:27,840 --> 00:21:30,480
is truly our golden year.

194
00:21:31,040 --> 00:21:33,160
We've finally got the farm in our hands.

195
00:21:33,920 --> 00:21:36,680
Na has a degree from abroad.

196
00:21:38,440 --> 00:21:40,040
And then there's Nee.

197
00:21:41,840 --> 00:21:43,360
Oh, please.

198
00:21:44,400 --> 00:21:46,400
Just flaunt the money around,

199
00:21:47,000 --> 00:21:50,320
and a good nephew-in-law
will come running to you.

200
00:21:53,960 --> 00:21:55,320
They'll probably

201
00:21:55,840 --> 00:21:59,760
jump at the money,
their tongues hanging out.

202
00:22:02,440 --> 00:22:04,560
Boss! Boss!

203
00:22:05,160 --> 00:22:06,120
- Oh.
- Uh.

204
00:22:07,760 --> 00:22:09,000
Why did you barge in?

205
00:22:09,080 --> 00:22:09,920
Oh.

206
00:22:10,000 --> 00:22:12,920
The live Thai boxing match
on Channel 3 is on.

207
00:22:14,240 --> 00:22:15,920
And what happened to you two?

208
00:22:16,000 --> 00:22:17,280
Umami.

209
00:22:17,360 --> 00:22:18,640
Did you get beat up?

210
00:22:18,720 --> 00:22:20,240
Does the dirt taste great?

211
00:22:20,320 --> 00:22:21,480
Ow…

212
00:22:23,520 --> 00:22:24,600
Or is it true

213
00:22:24,680 --> 00:22:27,440
Madam's selling the farm,
just as people at the market are saying?

214
00:22:27,520 --> 00:22:30,120
No way. She has no right to sell this farm

215
00:22:30,200 --> 00:22:31,640
Why not?

216
00:22:31,720 --> 00:22:34,840
Mr. Paisal passed away,
so the farm belongs to her.

217
00:22:35,760 --> 00:22:39,080
No. Uncle Win said the farm
actually belongs to his son.

218
00:22:39,160 --> 00:22:40,440
- Oh, his son?
- His son?

219
00:22:40,520 --> 00:22:42,280
The one who killed someone?

220
00:22:42,360 --> 00:22:43,200
- Huh?
- Oh.

221
00:22:49,320 --> 00:22:51,480
- Why are there sheep in the truck?
- Aren't those our sheep?

222
00:22:54,880 --> 00:22:56,000
Let's go see.

223
00:22:56,760 --> 00:22:57,600
Huh?

224
00:22:57,680 --> 00:22:59,520
- They're our farm's sheep.
- Yeah.

225
00:23:00,760 --> 00:23:01,920
- Whoo!
- And who's that?

226
00:23:02,440 --> 00:23:03,320
Oh?

227
00:23:09,640 --> 00:23:12,680
Well, it's good that you're all here.

228
00:23:12,760 --> 00:23:14,520
Open the pen and come help out.

229
00:23:14,600 --> 00:23:15,760
Hey, don't just stand there confused.

230
00:23:15,840 --> 00:23:16,800
Come on.

231
00:23:16,880 --> 00:23:20,000
Wait, wait. Who are you, seriously?

232
00:23:22,920 --> 00:23:23,880
You're Piak, right?

233
00:23:25,320 --> 00:23:28,200
- How did he know?
- And you're his wife, Waan.

234
00:23:28,280 --> 00:23:29,440
- Huh?
- Hey.

235
00:23:29,520 --> 00:23:32,040
- How does he know?
- You know who we are?

236
00:23:35,040 --> 00:23:36,440
Oh, here comes trouble.

237
00:23:37,240 --> 00:23:38,080
There he is, Boss.

238
00:23:41,920 --> 00:23:43,160
He's not with them?

239
00:23:47,960 --> 00:23:50,760
Was it you who took the truck
and tried to steal the sheep?

240
00:23:51,960 --> 00:23:54,040
Well, you’re exaggerating.

241
00:23:54,120 --> 00:23:56,440
Who would waste time
stealing their own property?

242
00:24:01,400 --> 00:24:02,720
What the hell does that mean?

243
00:24:05,080 --> 00:24:07,320
Foul language? So we're close now?

244
00:24:09,640 --> 00:24:11,320
Then why don't you go unload the sheep?

245
00:24:20,080 --> 00:24:22,160
- Ah! Ow!
- Hey, hey.

246
00:24:25,120 --> 00:24:27,080
Jerd! Kan! Get him!

247
00:24:39,360 --> 00:24:40,480
‪What's happening here?

248
00:24:43,720 --> 00:24:46,080
What are you all standing there for?!

249
00:24:48,480 --> 00:24:49,760
What do we do?

250
00:24:51,200 --> 00:24:52,480
Move, or I'll fire you!

251
00:24:52,560 --> 00:24:53,560
Or should we just quit?

252
00:24:53,640 --> 00:24:55,520
And how are we supposed
to survive? Go help!

253
00:24:55,600 --> 00:24:56,640
Go! Hurry!

254
00:25:15,160 --> 00:25:16,240
- I'm sorry.
- Hey, Piak!

255
00:25:16,920 --> 00:25:17,960
Careful, Piak!

256
00:25:22,000 --> 00:25:23,640
Ah, dear.

257
00:25:24,160 --> 00:25:27,520
- Are my jewels still there?
- Piak! I can't check right now.

258
00:25:27,600 --> 00:25:29,200
- Really? Ow!
- Slowly.

259
00:25:30,400 --> 00:25:34,120
- Can you take a look now? Still there?
- How am I supposed to check?

260
00:25:34,200 --> 00:25:35,720
- Ooh.
- Well?

261
00:25:35,800 --> 00:25:37,240
- Hey!
- Oh, a gun.

262
00:25:43,200 --> 00:25:44,480
Scared to die, aren't you?

263
00:25:45,360 --> 00:25:47,200
You're facing multiple charges for sure.

264
00:25:55,120 --> 00:25:56,880
If you draw a gun, you have to shoot.

265
00:25:56,960 --> 00:25:57,880
Remember that.

266
00:26:09,800 --> 00:26:11,240
Hey, tend to your husband first.

267
00:26:11,840 --> 00:26:13,680
- Oh.
- Ugh. You stood up so fast.

268
00:26:15,680 --> 00:26:19,560
QUICK LOAN

269
00:26:27,760 --> 00:26:31,400
They claimed everyone
could get a loan without any collateral.

270
00:26:32,800 --> 00:26:35,920
But when I applied,
they said I'm just a laborer.

271
00:26:36,000 --> 00:26:39,120
I don't have enough credit? Damn it.

272
00:26:40,680 --> 00:26:42,680
They treated you like that too, right?

273
00:26:43,320 --> 00:26:46,440
- Hang in there, Auntie. We'll find a way.
- Mm.

274
00:27:06,680 --> 00:27:09,440
Who's that? She's beautiful.

275
00:27:09,960 --> 00:27:11,320
Whose daughter or wife is she?

276
00:27:12,280 --> 00:27:14,760
She's the daughter of a maid
at Paisal Farm, Boss.

277
00:27:21,160 --> 00:27:22,120
Oh, Pin?

278
00:27:26,480 --> 00:27:27,800
What are you doing here?

279
00:27:28,400 --> 00:27:29,600
Thought you were visiting Aunt Un.

280
00:27:30,920 --> 00:27:32,680
I was just stopping by to buy some things.

281
00:27:32,760 --> 00:27:33,800
I'm about to leave.

282
00:27:33,880 --> 00:27:35,440
Then I'll go with you.

283
00:27:41,400 --> 00:27:42,240
Jom.

284
00:27:42,320 --> 00:27:44,480
Noi said there were thieves
who went to rob the farm.

285
00:27:47,160 --> 00:27:48,920
Do you think I'm a joke?

286
00:27:49,000 --> 00:27:50,760
Why are you saying such nonsense?

287
00:27:50,840 --> 00:27:53,520
What kind of thieves
would rob us in broad daylight?

288
00:27:57,600 --> 00:27:58,680
Teera.

289
00:28:01,440 --> 00:28:02,880
What is this?

290
00:28:04,640 --> 00:28:06,160
Call the police.

291
00:28:06,240 --> 00:28:07,440
This lunatic is causing trouble.

292
00:28:07,520 --> 00:28:08,960
He said he owns this place.

293
00:28:09,480 --> 00:28:11,080
What kind of drugs is he on?

294
00:28:15,000 --> 00:28:17,560
Shall we see which goes off first?
The trigger or the ringer?

295
00:28:17,640 --> 00:28:18,560
You…

296
00:28:20,600 --> 00:28:22,560
Don't… Don't shoot.

297
00:28:23,080 --> 00:28:24,200
Calm down.

298
00:28:25,560 --> 00:28:27,440
If you're in trouble, I'll help.

299
00:28:29,480 --> 00:28:30,520
- Noi.
- Yes?

300
00:28:30,600 --> 00:28:31,440
How much do you have on you?

301
00:28:31,520 --> 00:28:32,640
Give it to him.

302
00:28:32,720 --> 00:28:33,920
Ugh, I don't have any money.

303
00:28:34,000 --> 00:28:35,920
You haven't even paid my salary.

304
00:28:39,080 --> 00:28:42,200
Hey… Listen to me.

305
00:28:42,280 --> 00:28:44,280
I don't have any cash on me.

306
00:28:44,360 --> 00:28:46,000
I've deposited it all into the bank.

307
00:28:46,520 --> 00:28:48,280
Uh… Let's do this.

308
00:28:48,960 --> 00:28:52,000
Take a few items in here that you like.

309
00:28:52,080 --> 00:28:53,000
I'll give them to you.

310
00:28:53,080 --> 00:28:55,120
Consider it me helping you
in a difficult time.

311
00:28:55,200 --> 00:28:56,120
Alright?

312
00:28:59,600 --> 00:29:01,680
Are you treating me like a beggar?

313
00:29:01,760 --> 00:29:04,320
Maybe a shot or two for bullying me?!

314
00:29:09,320 --> 00:29:12,000
Auntie, count to three,
so I can shoot him.

315
00:29:12,680 --> 00:29:14,120
Or…

316
00:29:14,880 --> 00:29:16,600
Or should I let him count you down?

317
00:29:18,640 --> 00:29:19,880
- I'll--
- I'll count!

318
00:29:21,640 --> 00:29:24,920
The lady wins! I'll let the lady count.

319
00:29:32,400 --> 00:29:33,720
Please don't do it.

320
00:29:42,240 --> 00:29:44,440
Uh… One.

321
00:29:49,600 --> 00:29:52,240
Two…

322
00:29:52,320 --> 00:29:53,800
Hey!

323
00:29:54,600 --> 00:29:55,920
Don't do this.

324
00:29:58,200 --> 00:29:59,720
Did you fail preschool math or something?!

325
00:29:59,800 --> 00:30:00,600
- Three!
- Ah!

326
00:30:20,440 --> 00:30:23,200
He must be crazy… or drunk.

327
00:30:25,000 --> 00:30:26,080
Alright.

328
00:30:26,600 --> 00:30:28,400
Enough fun and games.

329
00:30:28,480 --> 00:30:29,840
Let's get serious this time.

330
00:30:30,520 --> 00:30:33,160
This one is brand new, bought online.

331
00:30:33,240 --> 00:30:35,680
I was looking for a target
to try it out on. Stand up!

332
00:30:35,760 --> 00:30:38,040
I'm up and standing straight, sir.

333
00:30:38,120 --> 00:30:39,560
Not you.

334
00:30:40,880 --> 00:30:42,880
I was talking to you, Auntie. Up.

335
00:30:44,000 --> 00:30:45,040
Now…

336
00:30:49,000 --> 00:30:50,160
What do you want with me?

337
00:31:01,840 --> 00:31:05,040
Hey! What are you going to do?

338
00:31:06,120 --> 00:31:09,360
She's old enough
to be your mother, you know?

339
00:31:10,840 --> 00:31:13,760
You really can't remember
this handsome face?

340
00:31:28,920 --> 00:31:30,000
Mr. Yai.

341
00:31:32,360 --> 00:31:34,360
I don't know who he is.
When you went to get a gun,

342
00:31:34,440 --> 00:31:37,000
he returned the sheep
and apprehended the manager.

343
00:31:37,080 --> 00:31:39,080
He looks like one of those junkies.

344
00:31:39,160 --> 00:31:40,560
This is too much.

345
00:31:41,080 --> 00:31:42,680
I don't know if he's crazy or not,

346
00:31:42,760 --> 00:31:44,240
but he can't barge in like this.

347
00:31:44,320 --> 00:31:45,120
Where is he?

348
00:31:46,240 --> 00:31:48,040
He's in the room. He's got Madam with him.

349
00:31:57,280 --> 00:31:59,000
There's no way I'll believe you're…

350
00:31:59,080 --> 00:32:02,080
It's fine if you don't remember
your beloved stepson.

351
00:32:02,600 --> 00:32:05,920
But surely you remember Pha, right?

352
00:32:14,480 --> 00:32:16,840
Or do I need to refresh your memory

353
00:32:16,920 --> 00:32:19,520
of what happened at the barn that day?

354
00:32:23,520 --> 00:32:25,480
Pha. Pha…

355
00:32:25,560 --> 00:32:28,120
Pha… I love you.

356
00:32:30,200 --> 00:32:31,560
You love me?

357
00:32:32,160 --> 00:32:34,240
But you left me in prison

358
00:32:34,960 --> 00:32:37,480
and enjoyed life with another man.

359
00:32:38,240 --> 00:32:43,040
You… You think I'm happy
sleeping with that frail old man?

360
00:32:43,120 --> 00:32:46,160
You know full well
why I'm putting up with this.

361
00:32:52,120 --> 00:32:53,160
1 million.

362
00:32:56,720 --> 00:32:58,720
And I'll never show my face here again.

363
00:33:00,040 --> 00:33:03,440
Where am I supposed to get a million from?

364
00:33:03,520 --> 00:33:05,480
That old man Paisal, obviously.

365
00:33:06,240 --> 00:33:08,080
He might be willing to pay

366
00:33:08,760 --> 00:33:11,120
to keep your disgusting scandal
under wraps.

367
00:33:12,400 --> 00:33:15,560
You only think about yourself,

368
00:33:15,640 --> 00:33:16,840
you selfish bastard.

369
00:33:26,320 --> 00:33:28,240
Mr. Yai?

370
00:33:34,960 --> 00:33:36,680
You two fooled my father.

371
00:33:41,760 --> 00:33:43,000
This kid.

372
00:33:44,840 --> 00:33:48,600
Should I silence him,
or should I kidnap him for ransom?

373
00:33:56,320 --> 00:33:57,200
Good.

374
00:33:58,040 --> 00:33:59,360
You like violence?

375
00:34:12,679 --> 00:34:13,840
- Uh…
- Pha.

376
00:34:15,440 --> 00:34:17,679
Pha. Pha.

377
00:34:17,760 --> 00:34:18,760
Pha.

378
00:34:20,159 --> 00:34:21,239
Pha.

379
00:34:28,960 --> 00:34:29,840
You…

380
00:34:30,639 --> 00:34:32,400
You killed a man.

381
00:34:32,480 --> 00:34:33,960
I didn't do it.

382
00:34:38,679 --> 00:34:39,600
Go ahead.

383
00:34:40,239 --> 00:34:43,440
Go tell your father I'm his lover.

384
00:34:43,520 --> 00:34:45,199
Too afraid to speak?

385
00:34:46,000 --> 00:34:48,040
Because if you tell your father,

386
00:34:48,120 --> 00:34:50,440
you'd be the one going to jail

387
00:34:50,520 --> 00:34:52,800
for killing someone.

388
00:34:55,560 --> 00:34:58,720
Run away. And don't ever come back.

389
00:34:58,800 --> 00:35:00,640
And I won't tell anyone

390
00:35:00,720 --> 00:35:03,120
that you're a murderer.

391
00:35:04,120 --> 00:35:06,720
You murderer. You murderer!

392
00:35:14,920 --> 00:35:18,400
I was so proud of myself for such
a long time, thinking I was a murderer.

393
00:35:20,280 --> 00:35:22,640
If I hadn't seen the evidence,

394
00:35:23,160 --> 00:35:25,520
I wouldn't have known
that Pha didn't die that day

395
00:35:26,040 --> 00:35:28,400
but was hit by a car later on.

396
00:35:33,000 --> 00:35:34,680
Did that catch you off guard,

397
00:35:35,200 --> 00:35:37,160
my beloved stepmother?

398
00:35:43,720 --> 00:35:46,000
Hey! Open the door!

399
00:35:46,080 --> 00:35:49,160
If you do anything to her,
you won't get away with it.

400
00:35:57,200 --> 00:35:58,440
Open the door.

401
00:36:00,280 --> 00:36:01,880
Hey! I said open the door.

402
00:36:02,800 --> 00:36:04,200
Open the door!

403
00:36:06,440 --> 00:36:08,240
Hey, it's quiet.

404
00:36:09,120 --> 00:36:11,000
Did he do something filthy to her?

405
00:36:13,520 --> 00:36:15,200
Piak, ram the door open.

406
00:36:15,280 --> 00:36:16,240
I've got you covered.

407
00:36:16,320 --> 00:36:17,160
Yes.

408
00:36:19,480 --> 00:36:21,400
One. Two. Three.

409
00:36:25,520 --> 00:36:26,640
Hands in the air.

410
00:36:26,720 --> 00:36:28,960
- Get him.
- No!

411
00:36:29,040 --> 00:36:30,800
- No. Don't do it.
- Please move.

412
00:36:30,880 --> 00:36:32,400
I'll take him to the police.

413
00:36:33,160 --> 00:36:34,520
It's all a misunderstanding.

414
00:36:34,600 --> 00:36:36,640
We're on the same side. Put the gun away.

415
00:36:39,800 --> 00:36:40,920
Put it down.

416
00:36:43,080 --> 00:36:45,720
It's been a long time, Win.

417
00:36:46,960 --> 00:36:49,920
Is the metal in your left leg
still causing you pain, Uncle?

418
00:36:52,000 --> 00:36:53,960
You fell and broke your leg

419
00:36:54,040 --> 00:36:55,960
all because you were teaching me
how to ride a horse.

420
00:36:59,680 --> 00:37:00,640
Mr. Yai?

421
00:37:05,880 --> 00:37:07,840
The police! The police are here!

422
00:37:09,320 --> 00:37:10,840
Who told you to call the police?

423
00:37:28,520 --> 00:37:29,720
No need, Chom.

424
00:37:31,800 --> 00:37:33,920
Uh, it's nothing, Officer.

425
00:37:34,000 --> 00:37:36,800
There's been a misunderstanding
between the old and new workers.

426
00:37:36,880 --> 00:37:37,880
We're all clear now.

427
00:37:40,160 --> 00:37:42,400
What do you mean? But you said…

428
00:37:43,000 --> 00:37:45,280
I'm sorry. I'll explain it to you myself.

429
00:37:46,040 --> 00:37:47,600
Everyone, get back to work.

430
00:37:47,680 --> 00:37:48,920
There's no issue now.

431
00:37:50,120 --> 00:37:50,960
Yes.

432
00:38:03,520 --> 00:38:04,840
What's going on, Noi?

433
00:38:04,920 --> 00:38:06,480
You said a thief broke into the farm.

434
00:38:06,560 --> 00:38:08,120
What really happened?

435
00:38:08,960 --> 00:38:11,080
Well, he was a robber.

436
00:38:11,160 --> 00:38:13,640
But now, he's Mr. Chakrit… I mean,

437
00:38:13,720 --> 00:38:15,240
Mr. Chalit,

438
00:38:15,320 --> 00:38:17,560
the heir to Paisal Farm!

439
00:38:18,720 --> 00:38:20,160
- Mr. Yai?
- Mm.

440
00:38:21,440 --> 00:38:22,760
Mr. Yai came back?

441
00:38:22,840 --> 00:38:24,080
Mm.

442
00:39:01,240 --> 00:39:04,280
What's up, gorgeous? We meet again.

443
00:39:16,640 --> 00:39:18,040
I haven't fully recovered,

444
00:39:19,480 --> 00:39:21,080
and you're gonna leave a second mark?

445
00:39:21,960 --> 00:39:23,680
How did you get in here?

446
00:39:25,880 --> 00:39:27,120
I came in like a thief.

447
00:39:28,760 --> 00:39:31,320
Anyone who gets in my way
will face a bullet.

448
00:39:31,920 --> 00:39:34,560
Why did you come back after running away?

449
00:39:34,640 --> 00:39:35,880
What else do you want?

450
00:39:35,960 --> 00:39:38,240
I've been running long enough.

451
00:39:39,080 --> 00:39:40,720
I think I'll just stay here.

452
00:39:43,480 --> 00:39:45,800
Don't tell me…

453
00:39:46,320 --> 00:39:47,880
you're impersonating Mr. Yai.

454
00:39:50,720 --> 00:39:52,960
Wow, your memory is terrible.

455
00:39:55,040 --> 00:39:58,080
We've only been apart for ten years,
and you've forgotten me.

456
00:39:59,880 --> 00:40:02,240
But I still remember you clearly…

457
00:40:12,160 --> 00:40:15,520
Puny Pin.

458
00:40:25,000 --> 00:40:26,920
Don't wander out again, okay?

459
00:40:34,280 --> 00:40:36,760
Who are you? Put Tuem down.

460
00:40:46,520 --> 00:40:48,440
Hey. Hey.

461
00:40:48,520 --> 00:40:50,760
Are you okay?

462
00:40:51,360 --> 00:40:52,480
Hey.

463
00:40:54,160 --> 00:40:57,920
Help! Help! Someone's hurt over here.

464
00:40:58,960 --> 00:41:00,080
Hey.

465
00:41:33,160 --> 00:41:34,440
What the hell are you doing?

466
00:41:36,200 --> 00:41:38,520
You're so puny,
and you're still acting tough.

467
00:41:43,960 --> 00:41:46,040
You're not hurt?

468
00:41:46,760 --> 00:41:48,440
I was worried you were going to die.

469
00:42:11,640 --> 00:42:13,960
My name's Pin. What's your name?

470
00:42:14,040 --> 00:42:15,480
I just moved here.

471
00:42:15,560 --> 00:42:17,360
Do you also live on this farm?

472
00:42:17,440 --> 00:42:19,280
Do you want to be friends?

473
00:42:24,320 --> 00:42:25,160
Of course.

474
00:42:27,080 --> 00:42:28,440
Let's play, Puny Pin!

475
00:42:35,160 --> 00:42:37,840
These two are my niece and nephew.

476
00:42:38,840 --> 00:42:40,920
Kids, greet Mr. Paisal.

477
00:42:48,600 --> 00:42:52,400
- Please guide and look after them.
- Of course.

478
00:42:52,480 --> 00:42:54,920
Pin, what's wrong?

479
00:42:55,000 --> 00:42:56,600
Why are you crying?

480
00:43:07,160 --> 00:43:08,200
Yai.

481
00:43:13,680 --> 00:43:15,360
Come greet Aunt Krongsuk.

482
00:43:19,040 --> 00:43:20,480
From now on,

483
00:43:21,560 --> 00:43:23,440
she will be your new mother.

484
00:43:38,560 --> 00:43:39,720
Mr. Yai?

485
00:43:41,520 --> 00:43:42,920
You've forgotten me.

486
00:43:43,000 --> 00:43:45,320
It's a waste of time
going down memory lane.

487
00:44:00,480 --> 00:44:01,680
Are you really so disgusted?

488
00:44:03,200 --> 00:44:04,920
Trash is trash.

489
00:44:05,880 --> 00:44:08,720
It just smells rotten
and is full of germs.

490
00:44:14,880 --> 00:44:17,560
Mr. Yai. Have you been well?

491
00:44:19,120 --> 00:44:20,800
Where have you been?

492
00:44:21,480 --> 00:44:23,120
How have you been surviving?

493
00:44:23,920 --> 00:44:25,840
Was it very difficult?

494
00:44:31,920 --> 00:44:34,640
Robbery, murder,
and looting were so much fun.

495
00:44:34,720 --> 00:44:36,960
A bit rough
when I was running from the police.

496
00:44:40,720 --> 00:44:42,320
You're always fooling me.

497
00:44:42,840 --> 00:44:45,320
But I'm sure you have a sense
of what is right or wrong.

498
00:44:45,400 --> 00:44:47,160
You would have never become a thief.

499
00:44:49,720 --> 00:44:53,000
The world today isn't
much different from hell, puny girl!

500
00:44:56,720 --> 00:44:57,920
Or…

501
00:44:58,840 --> 00:45:01,320
do you want me to pick up
from where we left off last night?

502
00:45:07,520 --> 00:45:09,640
If you know something juicy, just tell us.

503
00:45:11,080 --> 00:45:13,120
He chose to come back now.

504
00:45:14,040 --> 00:45:16,000
That means he must have been planning it.

505
00:45:16,080 --> 00:45:18,800
If he shows up in court
and says he's still alive,

506
00:45:19,320 --> 00:45:20,320
it'll be a mess.

507
00:45:20,400 --> 00:45:23,080
To a happy family! Cheers!

508
00:45:23,160 --> 00:45:24,360
Cheers.

509
00:45:28,240 --> 00:45:29,800
- You… Teera.
- Mr. Yai.

510
00:45:29,880 --> 00:45:31,640
You poisoned me!

511
00:46:12,240 --> 00:46:14,520
Subtitle translation by: Anan Pratchayakul
